This paper deals with the problem of constructing pseudorandom generators for read-once branching programs, which is a central question in computational complexity theory. The paper uses techniques from coding theory, probability theory, and Fourier analysis, which are typically studied in subfields such as complexity theory (cs.CC), cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG).
